"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-03-paris-2024-olympics-wakama-promises-better-dtigress-performance-against-canada\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  D'Tigress head coach, Rena Wakama has assured that her side will bounce back from the defeat to France.  The six-time African champions lost their second group game at the ongoing 2024 Olympic Games to host nation, France 75-54.  D'Tigress were expected to give the French a run for their money after they stunned world number three Australia 75-62 in their opening fixture.  The West Africans however put up a below showing in the encounter.  Ahead of the team's final group game against Canada on Sunday, Wakama said her players will put up a better performance.  \\\"While we are disappointed with the result against France, we are motivated to put in a strong performance against Canada.  \\\"A win will ensure our place in the next round,\\\" Wakama told FIBA.com.  Transfer: Barcelona midfielder leaves Hansi Flick's squad to join LaLiga rivals  Olympics 2024 football: It hurts - Mascherano explains why Argentina loss to France  D'Tigress maintain 8th position in latest FIBA women's rankings  FIBA WWCQ: D'Tigress star Macaulay named in All-Star team  D'Tigress captain Ogoke retires from national team  FG fulfils pledge to D'Tigress for winning 2025 FIBA Women's Afrobasket  2026 FIBA World Cup Qualifiers: D'Tigress rally to 101-84 victory over Philippines  FIBA WWQ 2026: Gallant D'Tigress fall 77-60 to Korea  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"